<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>The Fifth Book of Moses, called Deuteronomy</H2></CENTER><P><A 
HREF='index.htm'>Return to Index</A>.</P><CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 CELLPADDING=5  
WIDTH=90%><TR><TD></TD><TD><CENTER><H1>Chapter 6</H1></CENTER></TD></TR><TR><TD 
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V1><H4>1</H4></TD><TD><P>Now these are the commandments, the 
statutes, and the judgments, which YHVH your ELOHIYM commanded to teach you,    
that ye might do them in the land whither ye go to possess it:</P></TD></TR><TR>
<TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V2><H4>2</H4></TD><TD><P>That thou mightest fear YHVH    
thy ELOHIYM, to keep all his statutes and his commandments, which I command     
thee, thou, and thy son, and thy son's son, all the days of thy life; and that  
thy days may be prolonged.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V3><H4>3</H4>
</TD><TD><P>Hear therefore, O Israel, and observe to do it; that it may be well 
with thee, and that ye may increase mightily, as YHVH ELOHIYM of thy fathers    
hath promised thee, in the land that floweth with milk and honey.</P></TD></TR> 
<TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V4><H4>4</H4></TD><TD><P>Hear, O Israel: YHVH our    
ELOHIYM is one YHVH:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V5><H4>5</H4></TD> 
<TD><P>And thou shalt love YHVH thy ELOHIYM with all thine heart, and with all  
thy soul, and with all thy might.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V6>   
<H4>6</H4></TD><TD><P>And these words, which I command thee this day, shall be  
in thine heart:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V7><H4>7</H4></TD><TD>  
<P>And thou shalt teach them diligently unto thy children, and shalt talk of    
them when thou sittest in thine house, and when thou walkest by the way, and    
when thou liest down, and when thou risest up.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP> 
<A NAME=V8><H4>8</H4></TD><TD><P>And thou shalt bind them for a sign upon thine 
hand, and they shall be as frontlets between thine eyes.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD   
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V9><H4>9</H4></TD><TD><P>And thou shalt write them upon the  
posts of thy house, and on thy gates.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A        
NAME=V10><H4>10</H4></TD><TD><P>And it shall be, when YHVH thy ELOHIYM shall    
have brought thee into the land which he sware unto thy fathers, to Abraham, to 
Isaac, and to Jacob, to give thee great and goodly cities, which thou buildedst 
not,</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V11><H4>11</H4></TD><TD><P>And     
houses full of all good things, which thou filledst not, and wells digged,      
which thou diggedst not, vineyards and olive trees, which thou plantedst not;   
when thou shalt have eaten and be full;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A      
NAME=V12><H4>12</H4></TD><TD><P>Then beware lest thou forget YHVH, which        
brought thee forth out of the land of Egypt, from the house of bondage.</P></TD>
</TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V13><H4>13</H4></TD><TD><P>Thou shalt fear YHVH 
thy ELOHIYM, and serve him, and shalt swear by his name.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD   
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V14><H4>14</H4></TD><TD><P>Ye shall not go after other gods, 
of the gods of the people which are round about you;</P></TD></TR><TR><TD       
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V15><H4>15</H4></TD><TD><P>(For YHVH thy ELOHIYM is a        
jealous EL among you) lest the anger of YHVH thy ELOHIYM be kindled against     
thee, and destroy thee from off the face of the earth.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD     
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V16><H4>16</H4></TD><TD><P>Ye shall not tempt YHVH your      
ELOHIYM, as ye tempted him in Massah.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A        
NAME=V17><H4>17</H4></TD><TD><P>Ye shall diligently keep the commandments of    
YHVH your ELOHIYM, and his testimonies, and his statutes, which he hath         
commanded thee.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V18><H4>18</H4></TD><TD>
<P>And thou shalt do that which is right and good in the sight of YHVH: that it 
may be well with thee, and that thou mayest go in and possess the good land     
which YHVH sware unto thy fathers.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V19> 
<H4>19</H4></TD><TD><P>To cast out all thine enemies from before thee, as YHVH  
hath spoken.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V20><H4>20</H4></TD><TD><P>
And when thy son asketh thee in time to come, saying, What mean the             
testimonies, and the statutes, and the judgments, which YHVH our ELOHIYM hath   
commanded you?</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V21><H4>21</H4></TD><TD> 
<P>Then thou shalt say unto thy son, We were Pharaoh's bondmen in Egypt; and    
YHVH brought us out of Egypt with a mighty hand:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD           
VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V22><H4>22</H4></TD><TD><P>And YHVH showed signs and         
wonders, great and sore, upon Egypt, upon Pharaoh, and upon all his household,  
before our eyes:</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V23><H4>23</H4></TD>   
<TD><P>And he brought us out from thence, that he might bring us in, to give us 
the land which he sware unto our fathers.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A    
NAME=V24><H4>24</H4></TD><TD><P>And YHVH commanded us to do all these statutes, 
to fear YHVH our ELOHIYM, for our good always, that he might preserve us alive, 
as it is at this day.</P></TD></TR><TR><TD VALIGN=TOP><A NAME=V25><H4>25</H4>   
</TD><TD><P>And it shall be our righteousness, if we observe to do all these    
commandments before YHVH our ELOHIYM, as he hath commanded us.</P></TD></TR>    
